vice/PlaceOrder`:\n  - Normal: ~150,000 µs.\n  - Abnormal: ~40,200,000 µs.\n  - Impacted Pods: Both from `frontend` and `checkoutservice`.\n\n#### 3. **Errors from ProductCatalogService**\n- `Error 9005 (HY000): Region is unavailable`\n  - Associated with multiple requests from `ProductCatalogService` to its backend.\n  - Example Pods:\n    - Parent Pod: `frontend-0` to Child Pod: `productcatalogservice-2`.\n- Significant spike in errors occurring nearly simultaneously with the elevated latency.\n\n#### 4. **HTTP Failures from Frontend**\n- Instances of `HTTP Status Code: 500`.\n  - This error correlates with requests delegated to `frontend` services during anomalies.\n\nThese observations align with symptoms of contention, cascading failures, or service unavailability in downstream critical dependencies. I will now consolidate key findings into a structured format."}
